EazzZyLearn Session Report
Introduction

tspan.tspan: EazzZyLearn is a brain activity monitoring algorithm that enhances memory. It is based on the
neuroscientific principle of Targeted Memory Reactivation, first described in 2007. The technological
principle involves stimulating specific deep sleep brain waves with gentle sounds, thereby reinforcing
the brain’s natural memory consolidation process that occurs during those waves. In fact, this is one of

text.tspan: the reasons why sleep plays a crucial role in our well-being and cognitive performance!

tspan.tspan: Memory consolidation is marked by the simultaneous presence of Delta waves from deep sleep and

text.tspan: Sigma waves, which reflect the brain’s reactivation of memories.

tspan.tspan: On average, sleeping for 1.48 hours with the EazzZyLearn system increases cognitive performance by

text.tspan: 12.6% in 95% of the general population on standard memory tasks.

tspan.tspan: EazzZyLearn is not intended to diagnose brain disorders or conditions. If you suspect you may be

text.tspan: experiencing a medical issue, please consult a healthcare professional.

Sound presentations during deep sleep Delta waves
Deep sleep is characterized by predominant slow-wave activity in the Delta frequency range (0.5 to 4
Hz). EazzZyLearn stimulates the brain precisely during these brain waves. Delta waves are easily
identifiable due to their high amplitude of around 100 microvolts from peak to peak, but varying with
sleep depth and age).
